@startuml seq-theme-switch
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer — Sequence: live theme switch (no reload, no recompute).
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: the punch-line of this flow is that the theme
'' swap is a *single DOM mutation* (the <link href>) that triggers a CSS cascade
'' re-evaluation — NOT a re-render. A `note` over the document lifeline plus an
'' activation bar on the browser style engine conveys "everything below the line
'' is browser-native, zero re-frame work"; Mermaid cannot annotate the cascade.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Switch theme — `:theme/set` → `:theme/apply` (live, no reload)

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "ui.views\n(<select>)" as Sel RENDERER_TINT
participant "re-frame\nevents/fx" as RF REFRAME_TINT
participant "app.db\n(:ui :theme)" as Db APPDB_TINT
participant "<link id=\n vv-theme-link>" as Link RENDERER_TINT
participant "Chromium\nstyle engine" as CSS RENDERER_TINT

User -> Sel : choose "Spacemacs Light"
Sel -> RF : dispatch `[:theme/set "spacemacs-light"]`
activate RF
RF -> Db : `assoc-in [:ui :theme] "spacemacs-light"`\n(so the <select> stays in sync)
RF -> RF : `:fx [[:theme/apply "spacemacs-light"]]`
RF -> Link : `set! (.-href link)`\n`"css/themes/spacemacs-light.css"`
deactivate RF
activate CSS
Link -> CSS : new stylesheet → `:root` `--vv-*`\ntokens change
CSS -> CSS : recompute cascade: every\n`var(--vv-*)` in `app.css` re-resolves
CSS --> User : repaint (new palette)\n— **no component re-render**
deactivate CSS

note over Link, CSS
  `app.css` is structural and references **only** `var(--vv-*)`.
  Themes are pure CSS-variable palettes on `:root`. Swapping the
  one <link> is O(1) and leaves the DOM, the re-frame loop, and
  DataScript untouched. (Default = `spacemacs-dark`.)
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer / UI / DOM |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db (selected theme) |
endlegend
@enduml
